                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180909-136-off750 t18180909-136-crimeloc753"></join>. On or about: the 22d of July I lost the articles stated in the indictment-the prisoner worked in my dye-house. I got an officer, and called all my men together; the prisoner was the first man that was searched - We found eight duplicates on him, six of which related to the property.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18180909-136-person1118">JOHN</persName>
             M'DONALD. I am shopman to Mr. Baylis, who is a pawnbroker, and lives in Portland-street. On the 3d of July the taffety was pledged for 15s.; on the 19th the searf for 7s.; and on the 28th a curtain for 9s. The prisoner pledged the silk.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18180909-136-person1119">
                  WILLIAM 
                  BROWN EDWARDS
               <interp inst="t18180909-136-person1119" type="surname" value="BROWN EDWARDS"></interp>
